# Docs checkpoint governance — JonBeatz

When user asks for **"update project"**, **"update docs"**, or **"backup project"**:

## Backup ritual (interactive)

1. Follow **AskQuestion** gates per [interactive-workflows.mdc](./interactive-workflows.mdc)
2. **Do not** auto-run backup until operator confirms via AskQuestion
3. Default destination: `G:\Hermes_Project_BackUpz\JonBeatz` (override via `JONBEATZ_BACKUP_ROOT`)
4. Quick path (no prompts): `npm run backup:quick` → `jonbeatz-project-v{N}-{a-z}`
5. After confirmed backup, append row to **`.cursor/docs/Restore-Points.md`**

## Other docs updates

1. Sync command docs to `package.json` scripts — no guessing
2. Prefer minimal edits in:
   - `START-HERE.md`
   - `Agent-Runbook.md`
   - `MASTER-COMMANDS.md`
   - `Custom-Prompts.md`
   - `ReCall.md`
   - `Restore-Points.md` (milestones/incidents only)
3. Capture operational incidents as:
   - symptom
   - root cause
   - shortest verified recovery path
4. Avoid duplicated instructions — one source-of-truth pointer when possible

## Restore point row format

`| RP-YYYY-MM-DD-short-name | YYYY-MM-DD | Summary: branch @ sha, backup folder, version. Restore: git checkout <sha> or copy from G:\Hermes_Project_BackUpz\JonBeatz\<folder>. |`
